# Local {{Name}} Dev Environment

## Quick start

`docker-compose up`
This will bring up every service. API, App, DB ... all of it

## Env Vars

Create a `.env` file in the root directory (one above the services, same place as `docker-compose.yml`)

```
## API ENV VARS
API_HOST=api.{{Slug}}.local
API_PORT=3000
API_PATH=../api.{{Slug}}.local

## APP ENV VARS
APP_HOST=app.{{Slug}}.local
APP_PORT=8080
APP_PATH=../app.{{Slug}}

## DATA ENV VARS
DATA_HOST=data.{{Slug}}.local
DATA_PORT=3000
DATA_PATH=../data.{{Slug}}

# Postgres Config
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=somepassword
POSTGRES_USER=postgresuser
POSTGRES_DB={{Slug}}
POSTGRES_PORT=5432
POSTGRES_HOST=db.{{Slug}}

## General
NODE_ENV=development
JWT_SECRET=somesecretstring
SUPER_OVERRIDE=somesecretkey
```

